<task id="R7-008" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>xUnit tests — temperature override + per-node prompt override (FR-14)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <wave>1</wave>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>bff-api, testing, wave-1</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>007</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-14 (test coverage — temperature + per-node prompt overrides), Q2 KEEP</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs with ~5 tests covering: (a) temperature override semantics
    (Action.Temperature vs config-default; node ConfigJson can override Action), and (b) per-node prompt
    overrides via PromptSchemaOverrideMerger — Role / Task / Constraints / Output Fields. This is the
    Q2 KEEP feature: per-node personalization layers on top of Action defaults.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET test author. The merger semantics are owned by PromptSchemaOverrideMerger — these tests
    confirm AiCompletionNodeExecutor invokes the merger correctly + the merged values flow through to the
    IOpenAiClient call. Mock IOpenAiClient at the executor boundary; do NOT test the merger's internal logic
    here (that's covered by PromptSchemaOverrideMergerTests).
  </role>

  <goal>
    AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs extended with ~5 tests:
    1. ExecuteAsync_UsesActionTemperature_WhenNoNodeOverride — Action.Temperature=0.0 → IOpenAiClient receives 0.0
    2. ExecuteAsync_UsesNodeTemperatureOverride_WhenConfigJsonOverrides — node ConfigJson sets temperature=0.7 → IOpenAiClient receives 0.7 (NOT Action.Temperature)
    3. ExecuteAsync_MergesNodeRoleOverride_OverActionRole — node ConfigJson sets role override; merged prompt sent to LLM contains the node's role text
    4. ExecuteAsync_MergesNodeConstraintsOverride_OverActionConstraints — node ConfigJson sets constraints override; merged prompt reflects node's constraints
    5. ExecuteAsync_MergesNodeOutputFieldsOverride_OverActionOutputSchema — node ConfigJson sets output-field overrides; merged OutputSchema sent to LLM reflects the override per PromptSchemaOverrideMerger semantics
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="executor-under-test">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiCompletionNodeExecutor.cs</file>
    <file purpose="existing-test-file">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="merger-source">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PromptSchemaOverrideMerger.cs</file>
    <file purpose="merger-tests-reference">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/PromptSchemaOverrideMergerTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="sibling-test">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiAnalysisNodeExecutorTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="adr-038">docs/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — integration-heavy pyramid. Mock at executor boundary. NO Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;, NO DI-registration tests, NO ctor-null-check tests.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-14">Test coverage includes temperature override + per-node prompt overrides.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec Q2 KEEP">Per-node prompt overrides (Role / Task / Constraints / Output Fields) MUST be preserved. Tests confirm this contract from the executor side.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §8 TEST-MODIFYING">Override row — testing tag triggers FULL rigor unconditionally.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F">Test update obligation — this task continues the FR-14 obligation started in task 007.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038 §7 build-vs-maintain">Tests added are MAINTAIN-class — they verify the Q2-KEEP contract that the BFF honors in production.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>testing/xunit-bff-pattern</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/standards/TEST-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md</file>
